author: The Columbus Dispatch
title: High-school football | MSL roundup: Amanda-Clearcreek springs upset
text:
Amanda-Clearcreek 29, Logan Elm 28:   Brayden Neff threw a 13-yard touchdown pass to Colton Roark with 53 seconds remaining and Jordan Leasure ran in a two-point conversion as host Amanda-Clearcreek upset Logan Elm on Friday night in a Mid-State League Buckeye Division game. 
Leasure had 29 carries for 263 yards and three touchdowns, his first two scores giving the Aces (2-6, 1-4) a 14-7 lead in the third quarter. 
But Marcus Paul (166 yards rushing) gave Logan Elm (6-2, 4-1) the lead on a 50-yard TD run and Jacob Sheumaker punched in a 1-yard score for a 28-14 lead. 
Leasure, who had a fumble recovery earlier in the game, cut Amanda-Clearcreek’s deficit to seven on a 1-yard run, then blocked a field-goal attempt to set up the winning drive, and had an interception to end the game on Logan Elm’s final drive. 

Bexley 17, London 6:   Three forced turnovers led to 17 second-quarter points for Bexley and the Lions (7-1, 4-0) defeated host London (5-3, 1-3) in the MSL Ohio. Micah Fliegel and Sean Early scored on touchdown runs that were set up by a fumble recovery and an interception, respectively. Another fumble set up a 27-yard field goal. Michael Johnson ran for 179 yards for London, which lost three fumbles and two interceptions in all. 

Grandview 42, Madison Plains 12: Andre Readey rushed for 111 yards and Rhodes Jump rushed for 105 in leading Grandview (7-1, 4-1) to an MSL Ohio win over host Madison Plains (4-4, 1-3). Jump scored on a pair of runs in the third quarter. 

Whitehall 20, West Jefferson 7:   Earl Redman rushed for two TDs and Brandon Copley made two FGs, and Whitehall (4-4, 3-2) allowed only a first-quarter TD to host West Jefferson (2-6, 1-3) in the MSL Ohio.  

Hamilton Township 34, Bloom-Carroll 0:   Patrick Robinson completed 18 of 30 passes for 398 yards and four first-half touchdowns as Hamilton Township (6-2, 4-1) rolled past host Bloom-Carroll (5-3, 3-2) in the MSL Buckeye. Mike Phimmasone caught four passes for 103 yards and Wes Payne scored a TD rushing and receiving.  

Circleville 40, Liberty Union 7:   Michael Camp passed for 120 yards and two touchdowns, and Circleville (5-3, 2-3) scored all of its points in the first half in a MSL Buckeye win over host Liberty Union (1-7, 0-5).  

Teays Valley 38, Fairfield Union 0:   Quarterback Drew Pennington had 125 yards rushing and two touchdowns and Teays Valley (6-2, 5-0) shut out host Fairfield Union (3-5, 1-4) in the MSL Buckeye. Pennington, who had a 70-yard touchdown run early in the fourth quarter, also threw for 105 yards.  

Fisher Catholic 14, Fairfield Christian 7:   Allen McCall scored twice, including a 1-yard TD in overtime and Fisher Catholic (6-2, 5-0) won its sixth straight in an MSL Cardinal game at Fairfield Christian (3-5, 2-2). The teams exchanged touchdowns in the second quarter on a McCall 3-yard run and a Joshua Heeter 57-yard run for Fairfield Christian. Heeter finished with 82 yards rushing, but Fairfield Christian gained just 32 total yards in the second half. 

Harvest Prep 54, Grove City Christian 12:   Daniel Bangura rushed for 255 yards on eight carries and had three touchdowns for Harvest Prep (6-2, 4-0), which routed visiting Grove City Christian (0-8, 0-5) in an MSL Cardinal game. Bangura scored on runs of 65, 82 and 51 yards for the Warriors, who led 41-0 at halftime. 

Millersport 33, Worthington Christian 21:   Beau Thorne rushed for 189 yards and four touchdowns, including two in the fourth quarter as Millersport (3-5, 2-2) pulled away from host Worthington Christian (2-6, 1-3) in the MSL Cardinal. Mike Seeger had four receptions for 86 yards, including a 46-yard TD catch to tie the score at 14 before halftime.
